In this design challenge, you will create swirling swirls. This exercise connect your eyes, your brain, and your hands 
and builds real-time skills of evaluation.

Materials: 
- paper
- pens

Instructions:
Fold a piece of paper into quarters. In each panel, draw swirls such to your looking. Try to iterate upon the design and continually
draw more to your liking. This exercises your ability to create and indicates your understanding of aesthetic or artistic composition.

